# Watch Reference Patch 03 — Tudor, Vacheron Constantin, Breitling

**TL;DR**
- This patch (a) corrects every existing vintage Tudor entry to the canonical `/0` suffix form and adds five neo-vintage Tudor families (76100, 76214, 94510, 91514, 75090); (b) extends Vacheron Constantin's vintage dress and complication coverage with 12 references and decodes the modern Overseas `Bxxx` dial-suffix system; (c) provides depth-first coverage of vintage Breitling — Top Time (810/2002/2003 + reissues), Co-Pilot/AVI 765 family, the 1974–75 Italian-Army ref 817, and the 1940s Premier 777/790/791/787/795 family — plus a full parse of the post-1990 Breitling alphanumeric reference system.
- Two listings-database flags result from this research: **Tudor `7176/0` is not documented** in any reviewed source and should be treated as a typo for 7159/0 or 7169/0; and a Breitling Top Time **"Stag Beetle" 2023** release was not found in any reviewed coverage and is not documented here.

